{{distinguish|Aaron (Jaredite)|Aaron (Lamanite)}}
{{Religious text primary|date=October 2011}}
According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Aaron''' was a [[Nephite]] missionary and one of the sons of [[Mosiah II|King Mosiah]].  He was also brother to the prophet [[Ammon (Book of Mormon)|Ammon]].  As related in the Book of Mormon narrative, Aaron and his three brothers (Ammon, [[Omner]], and [[Himni]]), left their father, and his people, to travel to the land of the [[Lamanite]]s in order to preach the gospel to them.<ref>{{sourcetext|source=Book of Mormon|book=Alma|chapter=17|verse=6-8}}</ref>

During their sojourn there, Aaron was imprisoned and beaten,<ref>{{sourcetext|source=Book of Mormon|book=Alma|chapter=21|verse=13-14}}</ref> but eventually aided in the conversion of thousands of Lamanites, who later became the [[Ammonites (Book of Mormon)|Anti-Nephi-Lehis]].<ref>{{sourcetext|source=Book of Mormon|book=Alma|chapter=23|}}</ref>

